Certainly! To send values according to a sinusoid with a one-minute period, you can use the sine function with the appropriate angular frequency.

A one-minute period means the sine wave completes one full cycle every 60 seconds.

The angular frequency ω = 2π / T, where T = 60 seconds.

Here's your updated script:

```javascript
const mqtt = require('mqtt');

const client = mqtt.connect('mqtt://localhost');

client.on('connect', () => {
  const period = 60 * 1000; // 60 seconds in milliseconds
  const omega = 2 * Math.PI / period; // angular frequency in radians per ms
  const startTime = Date.now();

  setInterval(() => {
    const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;
    const value = Math.sin(omega * elapsed);
    const message = JSON.stringify({ value });
    client.publish('test/topic', message);
    console.log(`Sent message: ${message}`);
  }, 1000);
});
```

This script sends a sinusoidal value updated every second, with a period of 60 seconds.

